{"ESQUIRE":[{"def":"Originally, a shield-bearer or armor-bearer, an attendant on a knight; in modern times, a title of dignity next in degree below knight and above gentleman; also, a title of office and courtesy; -- often shortened to squire.","pos":""}],"ESQUISSE":[{"def":"The first sketch of a picture or model of a statue.","pos":""},{"def":"A suffix used to form feminine nouns; as, actress, deaconess, songstress.","pos":""}]}